{"title":"Distonia","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Neurología/UTD. Distonia-2025.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Distonia","guid":"cRmgWG82b1N9ru7lGM22Vg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"1. INTRODUCCIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Distonía = Trastorno del mov. → contracciones musculares sostenidas/intermitentes\\N→ mov. anormales, posturas o ambos.","guid":"YSE3lypI_-n_e3ptktrwqQ","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"✔ Mov. repetitivos, patrones torsionales, temblorosos.","guid":"KYW5KkdyTkNqCCCt6b6nNg","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"✔ Se agrava con acción voluntaria y activación muscular excesiva.","guid":"DqdDCvN6HSYkpHbqOVzttw","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"✔ Puede ser: hereditaria, adquirida o idiopática.","guid":"mxcmLsqHVbrc16gcODhSYQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"2. EPIDEMIOLOGÍA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"✔ Grupo heterogéneo → prevalencia variable.","guid":"C6yvVaxsQouWU_ikyihs1g","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"✔ Distonía focal = más común (ej. cervical).","guid":"s2ojDtFTnUBORQKPvAxIUA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"✔ Distonía primaria (aislada) = 16.4/100,000 pers.","guid":"jPzhrunk8QxTzqoNbxoPrQ","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"✔ Variante genética más común: DYT-TOR1A → 18-26/100,000 portadores.","guid":"_Kme3TOEI_E6bF5U3Yq5YQ","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"6","text":"✔ EE.UU.: 54,000-81,000 portadores → 16,000-25,000 con síntomas.","guid":"5MizazK0TSXdKcMMMHEsow","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"6","text":"✔ Subdiagnóstico común.","guid":"cSfHEg1eqw3elCta-AhQTQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"0","text":"3. PATOGENIA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"✔ No hay hallazgos neuropatológicos consistentes en distonía aislada\\N→ trastorno dinámico (disfunción neuronal, no degeneración).","guid":"spKZLEP3C1pW2liw3o63bA","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"3.1. Áreas cerebrales\\Ninvolucradas","guid":"VYNEWCGu24rulybzYGhsaA","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"🧠 Imágenes\\Nestructurales:","guid":"hsLo7hxoWG0Lsi2mZ0q8VQ","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Hemidistonía ↔ Lesiones en ganglios basales o sus eferencias (contralateral).","guid":"rOIunIxse04lMmsjZIRb_w","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"15","text":"🧠 Neuroimagen funcional (PET, fMRI)\\N→ actividad anormal en:","guid":"zi4mOuXciNE57ObFyPDiZQ","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"• Corteza motora","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"• Áreas motoras suplementarias","guid":"9rOtw26SFKHSK7OUqk6KTg","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"• Tronco encefálico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"• Cerebelo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"18","text":"• Ganglios basales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"15","text":"🧠 Modelo en red:","guid":"_hiIHFiydo-oeHFgIcz_aQ","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Distonía = trastorno de la red neuronal.","guid":"3hqvTOsqZ2-AWXq8p0_2eA","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• Puede haber disfunción en varios nodos de la red.","guid":"64dU_b8FttpfJ0nRzvKNMA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"27","parent":"13","text":"3.2. Estudios\\Nelectrofisiológicos","guid":"a-Tt17LCz-IgBVk33WjLmA","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• ⬇ Mecanismos inhibitorios centrales.","guid":"HyFOpZAYM7R8NTKUqJKkag","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"• ⬆ Plasticidad neuronal.","guid":"vdLcJfVTFRMB2LUUwNNCYg","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"27","text":"• ❌ Alteración en función sensorial.","guid":"03tq49qhIxjZSwZkHadDxA","children":[]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"13","text":"3.3. Registro con microelectrodos\\N(DBS en distonía)","guid":"3MPZJjJZLsSQebzwD5IeRg","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"• Alteraciones en tasas de descarga y respuesta somatosensorial en globo pálido.","guid":"3MSuqIErErDEkXmyuw_awg","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"• Patrón de actividad neuronal alterado → modulación dependiente del movimiento.","guid":"8mZEMmGyyyyJKJp1RdziPQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"34","parent":"0","text":"4. NEUROQUÍMICA\\NDE LA DISTONÍA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"4.1. Dopamina (DA) ⚡","guid":"7AwZnXnQLur73a2-neLFcg","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"• Hipótesis\\Ndopaminérgica:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"• Antagonistas de DA → pueden inducir\\Nsíntomas distónicos (reacciones agudas,\\Ncrisis oculógiras, distonía tardía).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"35","text":"• Enf. de Parkinson (déficit de DA\\Npresináptica) puede cursar con distonía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"35","text":"• Disfunción estriosomal → afecta\\Nliberación de DA → hiperquinesia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"35","text":"• DRD (distonía sensible a levodopa)\\Nrefuerza rol de DA en patogenia.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"34","text":"4.2.\\NAcetilcolina\\N(ACh) 💡","guid":"kl96e3UujlbnllsixWGLuQ","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Evidencia:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"• Respuesta a anticolinérgicos →\\Nespecialmente en niños.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"41","text":"• Modelos en ratón (TOR1A mutante)\\N→ alteraciones en vía dopaminérgica\\Ny función colinérgica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"41","text":"• Modelos DYT-TOR1A knock-in → estado\\Nhipercolinérgico en el estriado.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"34","text":"4.3. Otros sistemas","guid":"BYQ3bmb94c1br4VSxxfbcw","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• GABA, adenosina, glutamato →\\Nposiblemente involucrados.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"34","text":"4.4. Estudios\\Nemergentes","guid":"OqnOfU9qkWldprFx7c-LGQ","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"🧪 Proteómica plasmática\\N→ nuevas hipótesis:","guid":"SnO6r_skLFkMXpGqPks9ag","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Mecanismos inmunes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"• Alteraciones en\\Ntransporte de metales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"• Estrés oxidativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"49","text":"• Involucrados en distonía cervical,\\Nlaríngea y blefaroespasmo.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"48","text":"📌 Investigaciones\\Nfuturas necesarias.","guid":"TEmLLGEjjvaSPIejL-cGKQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"0","text":"1. CATEGORÍAS\\NETIOLÓGICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"✔ Hereditarias 🧬\\N(probada base genética).","guid":"0lvsmQy3Wdlwq-131N8QVQ","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"✔ Adquiridas ⚠️ (prev.\\N“secundarias”).","guid":"RJf9WBb9Oj_Fi4DQFL9KVA","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"55","text":"✔ Idiopáticas ❓\\N(causa desconocida).","guid":"EpXkIDXH1XJ8hQxCS7UBZA","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"0","text":"2. DISTONÍAS\\NHEREDITARIAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"60","parent":"59","text":"📌 Criterios:","guid":"vWLcKD8F9xR3ihl4gD3BIw","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"✔ Gen probando.","guid":"O_P7uKtj6AIM1cFm19nKRg","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"✔ Clasificación actual = mutación genética en vez de numeración (DYT-TOR1A en vez de DYT1).","guid":"6Wwcx7WbwDFqhW_Jmm70Gw","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"60","text":"✔ Se agrupan según fenotipo predominante y gen mutado.","guid":"Z7u_UOMjvWoKFQ4CzfHUCA","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"59","text":"📌 Clasificación por\\Nvías afectadas:","guid":"kin7psasCZjUnW58d8RIRg","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"1️⃣ Alteración en transcripción génica (KMT2B, THAP1).","guid":"x05XpjvL4pOTwDI_GVXw7A","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"2️⃣ Disrupción en homeostasis de Ca²⁺ (ANO3, HPCA).","guid":"HgrVllKAEOrXHsWYJDLZSg","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"3️⃣ Alteración en señalización dopaminérgica estriatal (GNAL).","guid":"sTLw6SFVZfZdUnuT0rsrog","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"64","text":"4️⃣ Alteración en respuesta a estrés del RE (EIF2AK2, PRKRA, TOR1A).","guid":"sNcd3yJnrjZePcbV62B-DA","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"64","text":"5️⃣ Disfunción en autofagia (VPS16).","guid":"HdVJyzIactiJeYweWhiZCQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"70","parent":"59","text":"✔ 🆕 Se espera que esta categorización facilite nuevos tratamientos.","guid":"WrPlNBw1YdNztizBB2YJdg","children":[]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"0","text":"3. DISTONÍAS\\NADQUIRIDAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"📌 Causas:","guid":"7tI-amimxz7Zd8jcD9fNaA","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"✔ Daño cerebral perinatal 🧠","guid":"xg4PygVNoE4qxOuqwxZSjQ","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"✔ Fármacos bloqueadores de R-Dopamina → distonía aguda/tardía.","guid":"BtrgLT1PdKXdP1D38oAMGg","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"✔ Lesiones en:","guid":"HEQzGJwNOCEerGbLJ9qUig","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• Ganglios basales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"• Tálamo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"• Tronco encefálico","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"71","text":"📌 Enfermedades\\Nautoinmunes:","guid":"MAEMaNm0quPOC77AfceGug","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"✔ Encefalitis anti-NMDA → distonía + mov. anormales + síntomas cognitivos/conductuales.","guid":"gvtI1FnWfVArX6BFOr440w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"0","text":"4. DISTONÍAS\\NIDIOPÁTICAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"📌 Definición:","guid":"EdxtHUbXrBRsCUnhJzIkoA","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"✔ Causa desconocida.","guid":"FAMFg9uVkrxn_ZB_R7fAGA","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"82","text":"✔ Mayoría de distonías focales/segmentarias en adultos.","guid":"YWvR5vw4LSSlvMFusc1mVg","children":[]}]},{"id":"85","parent":"81","text":"📌 Herencia posible:","guid":"6S8wzkSRJszWfQUoyGefIw","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"✔ Esporádicas o agrupadas familiarmente.","guid":"vFpl24rHjs1EigYGl6NdSA","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"✔ Si se identifica un gen, → reclasificación como hereditaria.","guid":"EX2PSCKNRbHLseK8ls3I1w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"0","text":"1. FACTORES CLÍNICOS\\NRELEVANTES PARA CLASIFICACIÓN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"✔ Edad de inicio","guid":"8fIfDymfpcESKg4EsR7zFQ","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"88","text":"✔ Distribución corporal","guid":"IzbU382U_wBoTh0MXeWWYA","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"88","text":"✔ Patrón temporal y dinámico","guid":"-oQBHmky3OBQSyjdYXDrXg","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"88","text":"✔ Características asociadas","guid":"awbAnFrte7A0KugIqGDeig","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"0","text":"2. CARACTERÍSTICAS\\NMOTORAS DEFINITORIAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"✔ Trastorno del mov. → Contracciones musculares sostenidas/intermitentes\\N→ Mov. anormales, posturas o ambos.","guid":"I3Z0nsGJNsdzhev6qm1yOA","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"✔ Mov. patrón torsional, repetitivo, tembloroso.","guid":"hqtCzCmStGmPvw0DU-k9YQ","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"93","text":"✔ Se agrava con acción voluntaria → “Overflow” (activación involuntaria de otros músculos).","guid":"vCf1t_FXzQehsS2oBI8yBA","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"93","text":"✔ Puede incluir temblor distónico (mov. rítmicos espasmódicos sobrepuestos).","guid":"G_XgwRlsCiVHbtqK4QJpbA","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"93","text":"📌 Excepciones:","guid":"bcFNDZYPGpiSg_DHwkfeTQ","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"✔ Blefaroespasmo y distonía laríngea → No hay postura anormal,\\Npero sí contracciones intermitentes que afectan función muscular.","guid":"eP413ZP0WuhWjKg_iCR7lA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"0","text":"3. CARACTERÍSTICAS\\NNO MOTORAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"📌 Impacto en\\Ncalidad de vida:","guid":"OcT8CZ_Bbc6fRm6w9IPVwA","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"✔ Ansiedad y depresión → Frecuentes.","guid":"UVmqy7t5ttMn86yRRPerHQ","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"✔ Alteraciones del sueño (insomnio, somnolencia diurna).","guid":"fKDVglEW-X8OksL0irkpEA","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"101","text":"✔ Severidad de distonía → Impacto en función social/emocional.","guid":"wB4rFoeOtVun4zvaQa-RBw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"0","text":"4. EDAD DE INICIO","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"📌 Importante para Dx y pronóstico","guid":"NcDZK_To1XrBVA3xcalFFQ","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"A. Distonía de inicio\\Ntemprano (≤20 años)","guid":"gSb73lK2Lyuq6S5gGq2ZJQ","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"✔ Infancia (0-2 años) / Niñez (3-12 años) / Adolescencia (13-20 años).","guid":"7PL19a1GIEURLZWwM_JO4A","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"✔ Más probabilidad de ser genética/idiopática.","guid":"QasQsg_rC4DIoJyqgb3lCw","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"107","text":"✔ Frecuente en piernas → progresión lenta a generalizada.","guid":"bytbFrWNnoEpm_zYrms9kg","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"105","text":"B. Distonía de inicio en\\Nadultos (>21 años)","guid":"4rXLBxa81p2XVkN96hOXJQ","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"✔ Adultez temprana (21-40 años) / Adultez tardía (>40 años).","guid":"uHrmLVxKQaxTZgwCrBO-jQ","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"✔ Frecuentemente focal o segmentaria → Afecta cuello, cara, brazos.","guid":"qfhEcdC6PaqS7IFuIfmTaw","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"✔ Distonía generalizada en adultos es rara → Sospechar causa adquirida\\N(fármacos, lesión cerebral).","guid":"oh1gsPy4WMDFDm_38mOsZQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"0","text":"5. DISTRIBUCIÓN\\NCORPORAL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"📌 Puede cambiar con el tiempo → Expansión a regiones contiguas o distantes.","guid":"7zgWnieVlc8gFZ9rq15vJA","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"✔ Focal → Un solo segmento corporal (ej. blefaroespasmo, distonía laríngea, calambre del escribiente).","guid":"j_L7GG_2mgdPORK5OKf8hg","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"✔ Segmentaria → ≥2 regiones contiguas (ej. distonía craneal, cervical y brazo).","guid":"UV08iLgnfn45WwZ-FzjDBg","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"✔ Generalizada → Tronco + ≥2 sitios más.","guid":"tl0bFRK-cNpjSufBKEBK3Q","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"115","text":"✔ Multifocal → ≥2 regiones NO contiguas.","guid":"Hi_V7qW0wrd59_jw_7tABg","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"115","text":"✔ Hemidistonía → Un solo lado del cuerpo → Causa adquirida\\N(lesión contralateral en ganglios basales).","guid":"4QTZFGibHohaZlXqIDjcgg","children":[]}]},{"id":"122","parent":"0","text":"6. PATRÓN TEMPORAL Y\\NDINÁMICO","guid":"wHeT7swk17EXc7sfDsPeOQ","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"✔ Específica por acción/tarea → Ej. distonía del escritor.","guid":"KG54Msyr7pRIQCwmpdqMbw","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"✔ Fenómeno de “Overflow” → Movimiento en una zona afecta otra.","guid":"Ovx7EPL2Kn7KeNZeC1ANDA","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"122","text":"✔ Variación diurna → Empeora en el día (ej. distonía sensible a dopamina - DRD).","guid":"C0432WXCQhd2wvbh0SujIQ","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"122","text":"✔ “Geste antagoniste” (Truco sensorial) → Maniobras que reducen síntomas (ej. tocar suavemente la zona afecta).","guid":"RK_cxV447Fzea8Jgw2ACQg","children":[]}]},{"id":"127","parent":"0","text":"7. DISTONÍA AISLADA\\Nvs COMBINADA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"128","parent":"127","text":"✔ Aislada → Solo distonía +/- temblor.","guid":"iYwPIEXgS-1uVuMav3DEtg","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"127","text":"✔ Combinada → Distonía + otro trastorno del movimiento (parkinsonismo, mioclonías).","guid":"8tKZy5EdCuXwDVaxcHKgJA","children":[]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"0","text":"8. SÍNDROMES\\NESPECÍFICOS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"A. Distonía de\\Ninicio temprano","guid":"uqS4yfcjS58tS6eO_cPvLg","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"✔ DYT-TOR1A (ex DYT1) → Infancia, progresión a generalizada, mutación en TOR1A.","guid":"Fe0iy8xsk7PT4T3E_hbbpQ","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"✔ DYT-THAP1 (ex DYT6) → Adolescentes, inicio craneocervical, penetrancia 60%.","guid":"EnUImG6jOaOJaC2p8fZhzA","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"131","text":"✔ DYT-KMT2B (ex DYT28) → Infancia, progresión rápida, discapacidad intelectual frecuente.","guid":"o6x6iPNSbUc2OrJXNwOpVA","children":[]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"130","text":"B. Distonía focal/segmentaria\\Nen adultos","guid":"rZiO4RUyt_PN0GBzQ8shxQ","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"✔ Cervical (tortícolis espasmódico) → Más común.","guid":"kIy2yyBbg6lfq7Ahmro5mQ","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"135","text":"✔ Blefaroespasmo → Afecta músculos perioculares.","guid":"CziJHwsEX8S6uwC4NlyVGw","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"135","text":"✔ Oromandibular → Mandíbula, lengua, músculos faciales.","guid":"9Tc9w5KoqaLYAMmqSQYF1Q","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"135","text":"✔ Laríngea → Interrumpe habla, más común en mujeres.","guid":"PcxsxMrSi_-6gfdm1VMNZw","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"135","text":"✔ Miembro superior → Calambre del escribiente, distonía de músicos.","guid":"xaqZpSbWWpr-bD3wCkdosQ","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"135","text":"✔ DYT-GNAL (ex DYT25) → Distonía craneocervical autosómica dominante.","guid":"cmjgbwFQmWQkfrwNIjYdCw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"0","text":"C. Distonía combinada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"0","text":"✔ Distonía-Parkinsonismo →\\NDRD, Enf. de Wilson,\\NPARK-PINK1-DJ1, Lubag\\N(DYT-TAF1).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"0","text":"✔ Mioclonía-Distonía →\\NDYT-SGCE, DYT-KCTD17.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"0","text":"✔ Paroxística → No kinesigénica\\N(DYT-MR1), kinesigénica (DYT-PRRT2),\\Ninducida por ejercicio (DYT-SLC2A1).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"0","text":"D. Distonía sensible a\\Ndopamina (DRD)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"0","text":"✔ Autosómica dominante\\N(DYT-GCH1) → Respuesta\\Nsostenida a levodopa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"0","text":"✔ Autosómica recesiva (DYT-TH,\\NDYT-SPR) → Responde a levodopa,\\Npero menos frecuente.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"0","text":"📌 Conclusión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"0","text":"✔ Clasificación basada en edad de\\Ninicio, distribución, patrón y\\Ncaracterísticas motoras/no motoras.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"0","text":"✔ Etiología genética vs adquirida →\\NGuía evaluación y manejo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"0","text":"✔ Distonía focal/segmentaria en\\Nadultos es frecuente y rara vez\\Nprogresa a generalizada.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"0","text":"✔ Tratamiento específico según subtipo (Ej. DRD\\Ncon levodopa, distonía cervical con toxina\\Nbotulínica, DBS en casos graves).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"0","text":"DIAGNÓSTICO DIFERENCIAL\\NY EVALUACIÓN DIAGNÓSTICA\\NDE LA DISTONÍA","guid":"aXs3_v52gCvib36eYDBAew","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"0","text":"1. DIAGNÓSTICO\\NDIFERENCIAL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"0","text":"1.1. Pseudodistonía\\N(Mimics de distonía)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"0","text":"📌 Movimientos, posturas o\\Nespasmos que imitan distonía\\Npero tienen otra causa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"0","text":"✔ Ejemplos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"159","parent":"158","text":"• Síndrome de Sandifer (ERGE en\\Nlactantes) → Posturas anormales.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"158","text":"• Tortícolis congénito.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"158","text":"• Subluxaciones atlantoaxial o\\Ntemporomandibular.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"158","text":"• Escoliosis severa.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"163","parent":"0","text":"1.2. Distonía\\Nfuncional\\N(psicogénica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"0","text":"📌 Puede ser focal o generalizada, pero\\Ncon características atípicas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"0","text":"✔ Movimientos\\Ninconsistentes, sin relación\\Nclara con postura/actividad.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"0","text":"✔ Ausencia de “overflow”\\Nmarcado (aunque puede haber\\Nleve en personas sanas).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"0","text":"✔ Posturas fijas postraumáticas\\Nsin causa estructural.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"0","text":"2. EVALUACIÓN\\NDIAGNÓSTICA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"0","text":"📌 Dx clínico basado en historia\\Ny examen neurológico.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"0","text":"✔ Confirmar si es distonía aislada o\\Nsecundaria a otra condición.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"0","text":"✔ Considerar prueba con levodopa,\\Nestudios de laboratorio y neuroimagen\\Nen casos seleccionados.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"0","text":"2.1. Historia clínica y\\Nexamen neurológico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"0","text":"✔ Edad de inicio y distribución\\Nanatómica → Indicios clave para Dx.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"0","text":"✔ Revisión de medicamentos → Fármacos\\Nbloqueadores de R-Dopamina (neurolépticos,\\Nmetoclopramida) → Sospecha de distonía tardía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"0","text":"✔ Patrón atípico →\\NSospecha de otra causa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"• Distonía en\\Ncuello/cara en\\Nniños.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"• Distonía en pierna en adultos →\\NSospecha Parkinson temprano.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"175","text":"• Distonía generalizada en adultos →\\NSospecha causa adquirida.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"175","text":"• Hemidistonía → Sospecha\\Nlesión cerebral contralateral.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"0","text":"2.2. Prueba\\Ncon levodopa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"0","text":"📌 Indicación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"0","text":"✔ Jóvenes (≤20 años) con\\Ndistonía focal/generalizada\\Nsin causa clara.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"0","text":"✔ Historia familiar de\\Ndistonía o parkinsonismo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"0","text":"✔ Adultos con distonía\\Nde causa incierta.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"📌 Interpretación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"0","text":"✔ Respuesta marcada y\\Nsostenida → Distonía\\Nsensible a dopamina (DRD).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"0","text":"✔ Respuesta parcial o nula →\\NDRD menos probable.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"0","text":"2.3. Estudios de\\Nlaboratorio y\\Nneuroimagen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"0","text":"📌 Indicación: Sospecha de\\Ncausa adquirida, hereditaria o\\Nneurodegenerativa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"0","text":"✔ Neuroimagen:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"• TC/MRI cerebral → Buscar\\Ncalcificaciones, necrosis en ganglios\\Nbasales u otras anomalías.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"• DaTscan (SPECT con\\N¹²³I-FP-CIT) → Útil en casos con\\Nsospecha de parkinsonismo.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"0","text":"✔ Laboratorio básico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"• Hemograma, electrolitos,\\Nfunción renal/hepática.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"• ANA, VSG, RPR (sífilis).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"• Ceruloplasmina y cobre sérico + excreción urinaria\\N24h + lámpara de hendidura (anillos de\\NKayser-Fleischer) → Descartar Enf. de Wilson.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"197","parent":"0","text":"3. PRUEBAS\\NGENÉTICAS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"📌 Indicación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"0","text":"✔ Distonía de\\Ninicio temprano.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"0","text":"✔ Historia familiar de\\Ndistonía/parkinsonismo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"0","text":"✔ Adultos con distonía\\Nde causa incierta.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"0","text":"✔ Pruebas\\Nrecomendadas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"203","parent":"202","text":"• DYT-TOR1A → Primera prueba en\\Ndistonía temprana, especialmente en\\Njudíos Ashkenazíes.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"202","text":"• Panel multigénico para DRD (DYT-GCH1),\\Nmioclonía-distonía (DYT-SGCE),\\Ndistonía-parkinsonismo rápido (DYT-ATP1A3),\\Ndeficiencia de GLUT1 (DYT-SLC2A1).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"202","text":"• Wilson (ATP7B) → Si\\Nsospecha clínica alta.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"206","parent":"0","text":"✔ Secuenciación de nueva\\Ngeneración (NGS) → Aumento en el\\Nrendimiento diagnóstico (10-20%).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"0","text":"📌 Puntos clave:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"0","text":"✔ Distonía en niños y adultos\\Njóvenes → Mayor probabilidad\\Nde causa genética.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"0","text":"✔ Distonía en adultos → Menos\\Nprobabilidad de causa genética, pero\\Nconsiderar Wilson o GLUT1.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"0","text":"✔ NGS y exoma/genoma completo →\\NMayor rendimiento en distonía con\\Nsíntomas neurológicos adicionales.","guid":"","children":[]}]},"node_count":210,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Neurología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Neurología","filename":"UTD. Distonia-2025","id":"map_1459","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"UTD. Distonia-2025"}